In this article, President Trump discusses various topics including immigration, the government shutdown, and the cancellation of the State of the Union address by Speaker Nancy Pelosi. Trump emphasizes the need for a border wall and criticizes Democrats for their stance on immigration. He also highlights the achievements of his administration, such as low unemployment rates and decreasing prescription drug prices. Trump accuses the Democratic Party of becoming radicalized and dangerous for the country. He expresses his disappointment with Pelosi's decision to cancel the State of the Union address and suggests that an alternative will be announced.